textAnnotation.text: This process is initiated when the customer is willing to order food, particularly burgers. At the initial step, the customer selects the type of the order from two defined options which are Burger-Only and With Menu. Depending on the selected option different tasks are implemented in the next step. If the option Burger-Only is selected, then the customer is required to select the intended burger. On the other hand, if the option With Menu is selected, the customer needs to select a specific menu from various menus containing different types of burgers such as Veggie Burgers, Buffalo burger, Barbecue burger, etc. Then, the customer is required to select a beverage. While the selected beverage is prepared by the robot, the customer is asked to select either Potato Wedges or French Fries as his/her side. It is important to mention that these tasks are done in parallel to eliminate the waiting time of the customer. At the next step, based on the selected option, the robot prepares the side for the customer. Then the customer is asked to make a payment (it is assumed that the payment could be done only via a bank card). After the payment, the customer enters his/her name into the system for status updates and notifications. Afterward, the system starts to prepare the burger and at the same time, the system checks the preparation status and updates the customer every 30 seconds. When the burger is prepared, the customer is automatically notified by the system and the burger is automatically delivered to the customer through a conveyor belt.
